{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox comedian | name = Jena Friedman | image = Jena Friedman in 2017 (cropped).jpg | imagesize = | caption = Friedman on January 18, 2017 | birth_name = | birth_place = [[Haddonfield, New Jersey]] | nationality = [[Americans|American]] | pseudonym = | medium = Stand up, writer, director | genre = [[Dark comedy]] | subject = | active = | influences = | influenced = | notable_work = | domesticpartner = | relatives = | academyawards = | module = }}
'''Jena Friedman''' is an American stand up comedian, writer, filmmaker and political satirist. She has been a field producer<ref name="medium"/> at ''[[The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]]'' and has written for ''[[Late Show with David Letterman]]''.<ref name="huffpost"/> She is currently developing a television project for [[Adult Swim]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/adult-swim-comedy-projects-jena-friedman-derrick-beckles-eric-andre-1202093188/|title=Adult Swim Sets Comedy Projects With Jena Friedman, Derrick Beckles & Eric Andre|last=Evans|first=Greg|date=May 15, 2017|publisher=Deadline|access-date=December 12, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Early life== Friedman was born in [[Haddonfield, New Jersey]] and was raised in a [[Conservative Jewish]] household.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juf.org/news/local.aspx?id=34066|title=What’s a nice Jewish girl doing telling jokes like that? |publisher=Jewish United Fund}}</ref> She studied [[anthropology]] at [[Northwestern University]]. After graduation, she worked as a healthcare consultant for consulting firm [[Booz Allen Hamilton]].<ref name="independent"/>
==Career== She has appeared on ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/11/election-results-stephen-colbert-trevor-noah-live-specials|title=The Moment Election Night Stopped Being Funny|last=Bradley|first=Laura|work=HWD|access-date=December 12, 2017|language=en}}</ref> ''[[The Nightly Show with Larry Wilmore]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cc.com/video-clips/laiik6/the-nightly-show-with-larry-wilmore-panel---what-s-driving-the-hillary-clinton-haters-|title=Panel - What's Driving the Hillary Clinton Haters? - The Nightly Show with Larry Wilmore |website=Comedy Central|access-date=December 12, 2017}}</ref> ''[[National Geographic Explorer]]'',<ref>{{Citation|title=Outsourced With Jena Friedman|date=March 8, 2017|url=http://channel.nationalgeographic.com/explorer/videos/outsourced-with-jena-friedman/|language=en|accessdate=December 12, 2017}}</ref> [[MSNBC]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc-news/watch/comedy-in-the-age-of-trump-890712131565|title=Comedy in the age of Trump|work=MSNBC|access-date=December 12, 2017}}</ref> and [[BBC Two]].{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} She has also been a contributing writer to ''[[The New Yorker]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/01/09/a-recipe|title=A Recipe|last=Friedman|first=Jena|date=January 2, 2017|work=The New Yorker|access-date=December 12, 2017|issn=0028-792X}}</ref>
In 2010, she received a [[cease and desist]] letter from ''[[The New York Times]]'' for parodying their wedding videos. The parody, titled ''Ted and Gracie'', has since become a popular web series. In 2007, she wrote ''The Refugee Girls Revue'', a satire inspired by [[American Girl]] dolls. The play earned critical acclaim in the 2008 [[New York International Fringe Festival]]<ref name="nytheatre" /> and had a successful run [[Off-Broadway]].
In 2015, Friedman's solo show ''American Cunt'', premiered in the [[Edinburgh Festival Fringe]] to critical acclaim.<ref name="herald"/><ref name="vanityfair"/><ref name="edinburgh"/> The magazine ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'' named ''American Cunt'' one of the 10 Best Stand Up Comedy Specials of 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/12/the-10-best-stand-up-comedy-specials-of-2016.html|title=The 10 Best Stand-up Comedy Specials of 2016|work=Paste|access-date=December 12, 2017|language=en}}</ref>
==Personal life== Friedman is a registered [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]. She resides in [[New York City]].<ref name="independent"/>
